OL,3,CCardiff to re-launch e-bike hire after
OL,4,Cprevious scheme axed due to vandalism
OL,6,FUp to 2,500 e-bikes could be rolled
OL,7,Fout across the city, with the option
OL,8,Fto add e-scooters in future, the
OL,9,FCouncil says.
OL,11,FHowever, this would depend on changes
OL,12,Fto the law around the use of e-
OL,13,Fscooters on public land in Wales.
OL,15,FCardiff Council says neighbouring
OL,16,Fcouncils in the Vale of Glamorgan and
OL,17,FNewport have also expressed interest
OL,18,Fin joining the scheme, which could
OL,19,Flead to a joined-up regional network.
